headline: Got $10,000? This Unique Nasdaq ETF Could Turn It Into About $1,000 of Income Each Year.
summary: The Nasdaq-100 Index is all about growth stocks -- it holds the top nonfinancial stocks listed on the Nasdaq stock exchange.  If there's one drawback to the Nasdaq-100, it's that it doesn't produce much income (the index's dividend yield is currently 0.8%).  The JPMorgan Nasdaq Equity Premium Income ETF (NASDAQ: JEPQ) offers lower-volatility exposure to the Nasdaq-100, and monthly income.
